parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SRS system can lead to the airbags not functioning properly in the event of an accident, potentially causing serious injury or death.
symptoms: The SRS light on the dashboard stays on
indicating that the airbags are not functioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling while driving can cause a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine dies unexpectedly while driving
the engine can restart but dies again shortly after
the vehicle may stall intermittently
the vehicle may not stall when checked by a mechanic or roadside assistance.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tread Separation on EPIC TOUR (LL600) Tires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected loss of tread on the EPIC TOUR (LL600) tires can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The tread peels off the tire without any apparent reason
such as hitting or running over an object
while the tire is still properly inflated. The tire may appear to be a retread
and the tread separation may occur suddenly
without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical wiring issue can cause blown fuses, dead batteries, and malfunctioning of the fan and air conditioner, leading to safety concerns and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: Blown fuses
dead battery
malfunctioning fan and air conditioner
irritating sounds from the fan and air conditioner
failure of tail and parking lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dealership's failure to properly diagnose and repair the issue can lead to continued safety concerns and financial losses for the vehicle owner.
symptoms: Repeated blown fuses
failure of tail and parking lights
malfunctioning fan and air conditioner
and unnecessary repair costs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden detachment of the inner fender liner can cause loss of control, damage to surrounding components, and potentially lead to accidents or electrical system failures.
symptoms: The inner fender liner detaches while driving
causing damage to surrounding components
pulling out wiring
and potentially leading to loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The damage to the wiring and electrical system can cause a range of issues, including loss of headlights, radiator failure, and potentially lead to electrical fires or complete system failure.
symptoms: Headlights are pulled out of their sockets
wiring is pulled out of the radiator
and other electrical components are damaged.
